<subSubSection id="89F434E23367FF8DFF5536ABFF443F40" pageId="51" pageNumber="52" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="C15167693367FF8DFF5536ABFF443F40" blockId="51.[151,1436,151,626]" pageId="51" pageNumber="52">
<emphasis id="F39ABB7B3367FF8DFF5536ABFEB43EB6" bold="true" box="[151,280,151,177]" pageId="51" pageNumber="52">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Small species, 3.4–3.7 mm; general colour brown, pale grey pollinose; frons yellowish; antenna yellowish, postpedicel brown, except at base, about 3 times as long as pedicel; palpus yellow; scutum with no vittae; legs yellow; wing clear; halter yellow. Male abdomen distinctly laterally compressed; tergites 3–5 with a number of flattened scale-like setae; sternite 5 with processes bare, longer than wide and little dilated at apices.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
