<subSubSection id="89F434E23367FF8DFF04374BFDAC3C4B" pageId="51" pageNumber="52" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="C15167693367FF8DFF04374BFDAC3C4B" blockId="51.[151,1436,151,626]" pageId="51" pageNumber="52">
<emphasis id="F39ABB7B3367FF8DFF04374BFEF93F96" bold="true" box="[198,341,375,401]" pageId="51" pageNumber="52">Comments.</emphasis>
According to 
<bibRefCitation id="A57F1A983367FF8DFE3F3744FD6A3F95" author="Malloch, J. R." box="[509,710,376,402]" pageId="51" pageNumber="52" pagination="225 - 239" refId="ref55116" refString="Malloch, J. R. (1921 b) Exotic Muscaridae (Diptera). - III. Annals and Magazine of Natural History, (9), 8, 225 - 239." type="journal article" year="1921">Malloch (1921b)</bibRefCitation>
, the male can be easily recognized among its congeners by its small size and by the peculiar flattened setae on the abdomen. 
<bibRefCitation id="A57F1A983367FF8DFC6D37A1FB3B3FB0" author="Paramonov, S. J." box="[943,1175,413,439]" pageId="51" pageNumber="52" pagination="505 - 512" refId="ref56537" refString="Paramonov, S. J. (1961) Notes on Australian Diptera (XXXI): A review of Australian Pygophora - species (Muscidae). Annals and Magazine of Natural History, (12), 3, 505 - 512." type="journal article" year="1961">Paramonov (1961)</bibRefCitation>
keyed the male, and 
<bibRefCitation id="A57F1A983367FF8DFF5537FEFEF43FDB" author="Crosskey, R. W." box="[151,344,450,476]" pageId="51" pageNumber="52" pagination="393 - 551" refId="ref53854" refString="Crosskey, R. W. (1962) A revision of the genus Pygophora Schiner (Diptera, Muscidae). Transactions of the Zoological Society of London, 29, 393 - 551." type="journal article" year="1962">Crosskey (1962)</bibRefCitation>
redescribed both sexes and presented an illustration of the male abdomen. According to him, the species is known only from 
<collectingRegion id="032AA98B3367FF8DFDCC37D4FD373C05" box="[526,667,488,514]" country="Australia" name="Queensland" pageId="51" pageNumber="52">Queensland</collectingRegion>
, 
<collectingCountry id="B9F927F93367FF8DFD6537D4FCB93C05" box="[679,789,488,514]" name="Australia" pageId="51" pageNumber="52">Australia</collectingCountry>
, but 
<bibRefCitation id="A57F1A983367FF8DFC8D37D4FC763C05" author="Pont, A. C." box="[847,986,488,514]" pageId="51" pageNumber="52" pagination="675 - 699" refId="ref57177" refString="Pont, A. C. (1989) 107. Family Muscidae. Pp. 675 - 699. In: Evenhuis, N. L. (ed.), Catalog of the Diptera of the Australasian and Oceanian Regions. Special Publications of the Bernice Pauahi Bishop Museum, 86, 1155 pp." type="book chapter" year="1989">Pont (1989)</bibRefCitation>
also mentioned 
<collectingCountry id="B9F927F93367FF8DFB5E37D4FAFE3C05" box="[1180,1362,488,514]" name="New Caledonia" pageId="51" pageNumber="52">New Caledonia</collectingCountry>
in the distribution of the species, based on the BMNH specimen listed above. As this is a single female, this record should be treated with caution.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
